# C++ Conventions

## File layout

Mirror header paths under `src/`:

| Header | Source |
|--------|--------|
| `include/model/Board.h` | `src/model/Board.cpp` |
| `include/rules/RuleEngine.h` | `src/rules/RuleEngine.cpp` |
| `include/engine/GameEngine.h` | `src/engine/GameEngine.cpp` |

Legacy root files (`Board.h`, `Game.h`) coexist during migration — prefer new layered paths for new code.

## Header vs implementation (strict)

- `.h` files are **headers only**: include guards, includes, type/struct/class declarations, member and free-function declarations, `static constexpr` constants, defaulted special members (`= default`), and member initializers.
- `.cpp` files hold **all implementations**: every function and method body lives in the matching source file, never inline in the header.
- Do not define function bodies inside headers — declare in the `.h`, define in the paired `.cpp` (e.g. `Piece::toToken()` is declared in `include/model/Piece.h` and defined in `src/model/Piece.cpp`).

## Includes

```cpp
// Header: guard, project headers (deepest layer first), then STL
#include "model/Board.h"
#include <vector>
#include <string>

// Source: own header first, then project, then STL
#include "rules/RuleEngine.h"
#include "model/Piece.h"
#include <iostream>
```

Never include outer-layer headers from inner layers (e.g. `model/` must not include `view/`).

## Comments

```cpp
// BAD — Hebrew comment
std::string capturedPiece; // "" אם אין אכילה

// GOOD — English only
std::string capturedPiece; // empty when no capture occurred
```

## Patterns

```cpp
// Bounds before access
if (!board.isWithinBounds(pos)) return;

// Parse: trim + istringstream; errors to stdout, return false
std::cout << "ERROR UNKNOWN_TOKEN\n";
return false;

// Extensible lookups: unordered_map + find, not switch on piece kind / similar keys
const auto it = rules.find(piece.kind);
if (it != rules.end()) it->second->isValidMove(from, to, board);
```

## Exception handling

```cpp
// Model: validate and throw — no try-catch
void Board::getCell(const Position& pos) const {
    if (!isWithinBounds(pos)) throw std::out_of_range("…");
    return grid[pos.row][pos.col];
}

// Boundary: catch and translate to DTO — no rethrow, no log
MoveValidation RuleEngine::validateMove(…) const {
    try { … }
    catch (const std::exception&) { return { false, "invalid_piece" }; }
}

// Top boundary: log once, recover
bool ScriptRunner::run(…) const {
    try { … }
    catch (const std::exception& e) {
        std::cerr << "Error in ScriptRunner::run: " << e.what() << '\n';
        output << "ERROR RUNTIME_FAILURE\n";
        return false;
    }
}
```

**Avoid:** catch-log-rethrow wrappers; try-catch around `toString()` or simple arithmetic; logging in `model/`.

## Avoid

- Raw pointers for ownership; use `std::vector`, `std::string`, `std::optional`
- Business logic in `main.cpp` beyond wiring and command dispatch
- Exposing mutable `Board&` to view or input layers
